        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 31 at 2:00AM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 200 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Fort Sumner, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Sumner and Taiban.

This includes Highway 60 between Mile Markers 326 and 345.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
